function [energy,pixarea] = var2energy(variance,numpix,screensz,res,vd)% function [energy,pixarea] = var2energy(variance,numpix,screensz,res,vd)%% computes the energy of a gaussian noise of a given% contrast variance and size. the result is expressed in degrees^2% of visual angle.%% parameters:%% variance-   the contrast variance of the image% numpix-	  the total number of pixels in the image% screensz-   a 2 element vector containing the width and %			  height of the screen, respectievely, in cm. %			  (i.e., [width height]).% res-		  a 2 element vector containing the width and %			  height of the screen, respectievely, in pixels. %			  (i.e., [width height]).% vd-		  the viewing distance, in cm.%% output:%% energy-     the energy of the image, in degrees^2.% pixarea-    the area of a single pixel, in degrees^2.if nargin == 5		pixarea = (visang(vd,pix2cm(1,screensz,res)))^2;	energy = variance*numpix*pixarea;else	error('not enough parameters sent.');endreturn;